text.section:
A licensed optometrist shall ensure that each replacement contact lens prescription that the licensed optometrist prescribes for contact lenses:
Contains all the information necessary for the replacement contact lens prescription to be properly dispensed, including but not limited to the:
Lens manufacturer;
Type of lens;
Power of the lens, including plano or zero-powered contact lenses;
Base curve;
Lens size;
Name of the patient;
Date the prescription was given to the patient;
Name and office location of the licensed optometrist who writes the replacement contact lens prescription; and
Expiration date of the replacement contact lens prescription; and
Is reduced to writing and placed in the patient's permanent file.
